As of Java 8, you can do this without Guava.  It&#39;s a bit clunky because [Iterable doesn&#39;t directly provide streams](https://stackoverflow.com/q/23114015/3614835), requiring the use of StreamSupport, but it doesn&#39;t require creating a new collection like the code in the question.

    private static &lt;T&gt; Iterable&lt;T&gt; concat(Iterable&lt;? extends Iterable&lt;T&gt;&gt; foo) {
        return () -&gt; StreamSupport.stream(foo.spliterator(), false)
            .flatMap(i -&gt; StreamSupport.stream(i.spliterator(), false))
            .iterator();
    }

